          <!-- Impact, Validation & Next Steps -->
          <div id="impact" class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-h2 font-primary font-bold mb-6 text-main">
              Impact, Validation & Next Steps
            </h2>
            <p class="text-body font-primary text-main leading-relaxed mb-6">
              The redesign simplifies the journey, improves clarity for first-time users, and reinforces trust through educational
              onboarding.
            </p>
            <p class="text-body font-primary text-main leading-relaxed mb-6">
              As this was a 1-week project, subsequent usability tests are needed to validate:
            </p>
            <ul class="text-body font-primary text-main leading-relaxed space-y-2 list-disc ml-6 pl-2 mb-8">
              <li>Tasks success rate</li>
              <li>Clarity perspection</li>
              <li>Trust level</li>
            </ul>
            <h3 class="text-h3 font-primary font-bold text-main mb-4">
              Next steps
            </h3>
            <p class="text-body font-primary text-main leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Moving forward, there are key opportunities to extend the redesign beyond clarity and trust, enhancing functionality
              and personalization for users with different safety needs.
            </p>
            <ul class="text-body font-primary text-main leading-relaxed space-y-2 list-disc ml-6 pl-2 mb-8">
              <li>Allow users to book directly through the app or connect with existing booking platforms</li>
              <li>Enable a direct chat with restaurants so users can ask safety-related questions before booking</li>
              <li>Allow users and reviewers to indicate their level of cross-contamination tolerance, making reviews more relevant and personalised</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <!-- Reflection & Learnings -->
          <div id="learnings" class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-h2 font-primary font-bold text-main mb-6">
              Reflection & Learnings
            </h2>
            <p class="text-body font-primary text-main leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Designing for health conditions means designing for emotional safety, not just usability. Simplifying pages and sections proved more complex than expected. User stories were essential to stay focused on what truly matters. As Steve Krug says, <i>be ruthless in what you cut</i> (and it's harder than it sounds).
            </p>
            <p class="text-body font-primary text-main leading-relaxed">
              This exercise was a great opportunity to sharpen my skills as a Product Designer. Working within a 1-week timeline pushed me to think fast, prioritise what matters, and tackle a different kind of design challenge, keeping me sharp and helping me grow beyond my usual work.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Navigation -->
          <div class="pt-8">
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <a href="../../"
                class="text-body font-primary text-grey hover:text-main transition duration-300">
                ← Back to Portfolio
